evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "Run ```sudo make install``` to install the graphmap binary to ```/usr/bin```."
"GraphMap2 - A highly sensitive and accurate mapper for long, error-prone reads" and usage examples show it as a command-line tool users run (e.g. `./graphmap2 align ...`).

Installation and use are described via cloning and building from GitHub: `git clone https://github.com/lbcb-sci/graphmap2` followed by `make` and running binaries, indicating source-repo-based distribution.
